Scotland's independent schools have a zippered performance of academic excellence, and it continued in 2018 with another set of excellent exam results, which were only reinforced by individual and collective successes in sports, art, music and other community enterprises.
With more than 30,000 students across Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Council for Independent Schools (SCIS), strive to deliver the best level of service to their students and parents.
Independent schools aim to prepare their students for further and higher education, their chosen careers and their position as world citizens.
